SIMPLE: mediate
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mediate
<hw>Me"di*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mediatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>mediare</ets>, v. t., to halve, v.
i., to be in the middle. See <er>Mid</er>, and cf.
<er>Moiety</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being between the two extremes;
middle; interposed; intervening; intermediate.</def>
<rj><au>Prior.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Acting by means, or by an intervening cause or
instrument; not direct or immediate; acting or suffering through an
intervening agent or condition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Gained or effected by a medium or condition.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An act of <qex>mediate</qex> knowledge is complex.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mediate
<hw>Me"di*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Mediated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Mediating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>mediatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>mediare</ets> to mediate. See
<er>Mediate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To be in the middle, or between two; to
intervene.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To interpose between parties, as the equal friend of
each, esp. for the purpose of effecting a reconciliation or agreement;
<as>as, to <ex>mediate</ex> between nations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mediate
<hw>Me"di*ate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To effect by
mediation or interposition; to bring about as a mediator, instrument, or
means; <as>as, to <ex>mediate</ex> a peace</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To divide into two equal parts.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Holder.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mediately</ent>⟦br⟧
